can do it using
   *synchronous 
   *asynchronous
READING A FILE:
        synchronous:
        var data=fs.readFileSync('filename)
        asynchronous:
        fs.readFile('filename',function(err,data));

WRITING A FILE:
        fs.writeFile('filenmae','msg to be written',function(err))
        disadvantage:
               *if we insert new content old content will get erased

APPEND A FILE:
        fs.appendFile('filename','msg to be appended',function(err))


RENAME A FILE:
        fs.rename('filename1','new filename',function(err))

DELETE A FILE:
        fs.unlink('filename',function(err))
OPEN A FILE:
        fs.open('filename','read/write/append',function(err,data))

